{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a443d8cc-77b2-4792-9672-dab3c630e69b","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but with important caveats:\n\n**Problems with your current targets:**\n\n| Target | Issue |\n|--------|-------|\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Not supported** by MSTest v3. You must upgrade to `net6.0` or later. |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Not supported** by MSTest v3. .NET 5 is out of support; upgrade to `net6.0`+. |\n| `net462` | ✅ Still supported. |\n\n**What to do:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with a supported target like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n2. Update your package references — MSTest v3 uses a single meta-package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n   ```\n   This replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n\n**Other breaking changes to watch for:**\n- Some deprecated attributes/APIs were removed.\n- `DeploymentItem` behavior changed.\n- Test class/method lifecycle defaults may differ (e.g., class cleanup timing).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"33e84580-a9f5-40d5-a68a-3c28c4ed9f52","outputTokens":336,"requestId":"981A:180764:43F6EA:58CDB1:69FFF2DC"},"id":"0e8c187c-2781-49f6-84d6-946397b2f5cb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:52:20.703Z","parentId":"54f75304-36dc-41a9-8950-b5f82c597f9c"}
